        &lt;figcaption&gt;Yup, it’s still there. | Image: Apple&lt;/figcaption&gt;
    &lt;/figure&gt;

  &lt;p id="An3iHv"&gt;Apple’s &lt;a href="https://www.theverge.com/2024/10/28/24275569/apple-usb-c-magic-keyboard-mouse-trackpad-no-lightning"&gt;new USB-C-equipped Magic Mouse&lt;/a&gt; somehow still has the charging port on the bottom. While Apple could have used the launch as an opportunity to move the charging port from the underside of the device — where the port has remained for nearly a decade, despite &lt;a href="https://www.theverge.com/2022/3/8/22967472/apple-black-magic-trackpad-peripherals-mouse-charging"&gt;other&lt;/a&gt; &lt;a href="https://www.theverge.com/2021/4/20/22394034/apple-new-imac-m1-chip-colors-design-specs-price-release-date"&gt;updates&lt;/a&gt; to the mouse and &lt;a href="https://www.theverge.com/2021/4/20/22394552/apple-new-magic-mouse-charging-port-bottom-lightning"&gt;being&lt;/a&gt; &lt;a href="https://www.theverge.com/22967776/apple-magic-mouse-charging-port-bottom-upside-down-its-2022"&gt;mocked&lt;/a&gt; for the decision — the port is still there.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p id="kH8qJS"&gt;This &lt;a href="https://apple.sjv.io/c/482924/1683292/7613?subId1=veergeappleproducts102824&amp;amp;u=https%3A%2F%2Fwww.apple.com%2Fshop%2Fproduct%2FMXK63AM%2FA%2Fmagic-mouse-usb%25E2%2580%2591c-black-multi-touch-surface" rel="sponsored nofollow noopener" target="_blank"&gt;new $99 Magic Mouse&lt;/a&gt; means that, for the foreseeable future, Apple still thinks that the best way to charge your Magic Mouse is by flipping it over to plug it in, making it so you can’t use it. Why?&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p id="04zeRe"&gt;There have been other solutions to the ridiculous Magic Mouse charging situation. For example, my colleague Wes Davis wrote about an ergonomic grip for the Magic Mouse 2 that can &lt;a href="https://www.theverge.com/2024/1/21/24045324/apple-magic-mouse-wireless-charging-lightning-base"&gt;charge the...&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
